{
  "schema_version": 1,
  "name": "Tritone Spectral Machine",
  "mood": "Foundation",
  "engines": [
    "Ouie"
  ],
  "author": "XO_OX Designs",
  "tier": "transcendental",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "Both voices on FM. Voice 1: ratio 1.414 (square root of 2 — the equal-tempered tritone), index 1.5. Voice 2: ratio 7.07 (5x tritone), index 0.8. The tritone ratio produces inherently dissonant, metallic tones that are the basis of bell and gong synthesis. HAMMER at -0.15 adds subtle ring modulation between the two FM voices, creating sum-and-difference tones from already inharmonic spectra. The result is dense, metallic, and unlike any single FM operator patch.",
